revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== {{suffix|en|xylorimba|ist}} ===Noun=== {{en-noun}} # {{lb|en|rare}} Someone who plays a [[xylorimba]]. #* '''1929''', ''Boys' Life'' (October 1929, page 54) #*: As a '''xylorimbist''' you put new pep into any party — "make" the school orchestra — maybe even pay your way through college. #* '''1999''', Howard Jacobson, ''Peeping Tom'' (page 207) #*: She did not belong either to that gentler but more rhapsodic band who seek to extract strange worshipful music from the male, the '''xylorimbists''' or tympanists or flute players.
